    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "Pdb is the debugger class. The completekey, stdin and stdout arguments are passed to the underlying cmd.Cmd class; see the description there. The skip argument, if given, must be an iterable of glob-style module name patterns. The debugger will not step into frames that originate in a module that matches one of these patterns. [1] By default, Pdb sets a handler for the SIGINT signal (which is sent when the user presses Ctrl-C on the console) when you give a continue command. This allows you t..."
